               <msContents>
                  <summary>Main Works: F<locus target="#1r"/>-Varia: Ff. i v(erso)-iv v(erso): Mazmur chants for the consecration of a new church. Ff. v r(ecto): Calendar of the Mazmur chants for the whole year. F<locus target="#1r"/>-115v: Chants called Mǝ‘raf, ምዕራፍ፡, organized according to seasons of the church year and for the celebration of saints, fasting season (57r), etc., with musical notation. Some larger sections include, Gate of Light (21v) set to music, Flight to Egypt (28v) and Praises of Mary (94r-100v) set to music, Mystagogia (114r) set to music, .  Me‘erāf I and II; AṢZ 103–246. Notes: F. i r(ecto): crude harags. Notes.  <locus target="#115v"/>: Record: Note of ownership: ወልደ ኤልያስ <locus target="#116r"/>: Record: Note of secondary ownership: "This book belongs the church of Saint Mika'el and was given by ወልዳ ኤዎስጣቴዎስ."</summary>
